result.execSummary:
The defendant James C Castro Sr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all prison wages at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.
Defendant shall seek and maintain full time employment.

Defendant shall have no contact with the victim-D.H.S., date of birth 5-26-1990 or any of her family.

Defendant shall not have any contact with any past co-defendants, known drug associates or gang members.  

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription and then take medication as prescribed.  

Defendant shall not enter into any establishment whose primary purpose of business is sale or consumption of alcohol.

Defendant shall not operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license or proof of insurance.  

Defendant shall not possess or use a computer or any technological device including a cell phone with internet capabilities without prior agent approval.

Defendant shall not possess, view, buy, manufacture any sexually explicit material or pornography, nor frequent any strip clubs, dance clubs or gentlemens clubs.

Defendant shall not enter, frequent, attend or be on the premise or grounds of any school, park, festival, fair, daycare, boys or girls club, YMCA, without prior agent approval.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent and comply with treatment recommendations, including but not limited to medications prescribed and sex offender treatment.

Defendant shall pay any supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

Defendant shall maintain a stable residence.

Defendant shall provide proof of all incoming and outgoing monies.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample within 3 days.

Defendant shall cooperate with the Sex Offender Registry and all applicable Sex Offender Laws.
